        "baseRefName": "master",
        "body": "This generalizes two results about vectors to matrices:\r\n* `dotProduct_star_self_eq_zero` to `conjTranspose_mul_self_eq_zero` \r\n* `dotProduct_self_star_eq_zero` to `self_mul_conjTranspose_eq_zero`\r\n\r\nIt also adds lemmas linking the kernel (under left-multiplication, right-multiplication, `vecMul`, and `mulVec`) of $A$, $A^HA$, and $AA^H$.\r\n\r\nSome of these lemmas are used in the SVD decomposition theorem of R or C matrices #6042 \r\n\r\n\r\n---\r\n<!-- The text above the `---` will become the commit message when your\r\nPR is merged. Please leave a blank newline before the `---`, otherwise\r\nGitHub will format the text above it as a title.\r\n\r\nTo indicate co-authors, include lines at the bottom of the commit message\r\n(that is, before the `---`) using the following format:\r\n\r\nCo-authored-by: Author Name <author@email.com>\r\n\r\nAny other comments you want to keep out of the PR commit should go\r\nbelow the `---`, and placed outside this HTML comment, or else they\r\nwill be invisible to reviewers.\r\n\r\nIf this PR depends on other PRs, please list them below this comment,\r\nusing the following format:\r\n- [ ] depends on: #abc [optional extra text]\r\n- [ ] depends on: #xyz [optional extra text]\r\n-->\r\n\r\nold description:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n> Three lemmas:\r\n> \r\n> - `conjTranspose_mul_self_eq_zero_iff` : a matrix is zero iff its conjugate transpose multiplied by the matrix is zero.\r\n> - `ker_conj_transpose_mul_self_eq_ker` : The Kernel of a matrix $A$ and the matrix $A^HA$ are the same.\r\n> - `ker_self_mul_conj_transpose_eq_ker_conj_transpose` : The Kernel of a matrix $A^H$ and the matrix multiplied by conjugate transpose $AA^H$ are the same.\r\n\r\n[![Open in Gitpod](https://gitpod.io/button/open-in-gitpod.svg)](https://gitpod.io/from-referrer/)\r\n",
